CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 20, 1940, pg. 9. reads: "In Pittsburgh for the Fashion Parade of the YMCA, these three smart Chicagoans expressed happiness over their week-end visit. in center is Marva Louis, to her right, Miss Audrey Hinton: left, Mrs. Harriett Jackson.  They are pictured as they boarded their TWA ship for the Windy City Sunday afternoon.  The show was one of the greatest ever given in Pittsburgh...over 1500 people braved the snow and cold winds to see the spectacular exhibit of fashions in which 52 girls and women participated. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Three women wearing fur coats and hats, posed on stairs of TWA airplane
